summaries.short: Aria, Max, and Clara plunge into a botanical Quick Craft and an upcycling Craft Master Challenge.
summaries.full: Aria, Max, and Clara think outside the box to create handmade plants and flowers before the two remaining crafters tackle an upcycling Craft Master Challenge that finds them transforming trashcans full of waste materials into something magical. Guest judge Anjelika Temple has some tough decisions in store.

summaries.short: Chuk, Suhani, and Lily get their hands “slime-y” with a tantalizing Quick Craft before creating life-size doll boxes.
summaries.full: Chuk, Suhani, and Lily have their work cut out for them with a sticky Quick Craft inspired by guest judge Karina Garcia, the “Slime Queen.” Using Karina’s favorite gooey ingredient, our crafters whip up fake food that looks good enough to eat. The two top chefs then tackle a daunting challenge: create life-size doll boxes that tell a story about who they are.

summaries.short: Weber, Brooklyn, and Ceres transform lockers and backpacks into creative masterpieces.
summaries.full: Weber, Brooklyn, and Ceres plunge into two school-inspired challenges: first, they transform lockers into creative masterpieces, and next, the top Craftestants turn ordinary backpacks into something super special. Guest judge Jodi Levine helps determine which crafter will take home the Craftrophia.

summaries.short: Kaya, Angel, and Erin spook the judges with Halloween-themed mobiles before the two creepiest crafters design light-up costumes too scary to wear.
summaries.full: 15-year-old Californians Kaya, Angel, and Erin spook the judges with Halloween-inspired mobiles before taking their shot at a Craft Master Challenge so wicked it’ll give you head-to-toe chills. As the two creepiest Craftestants construct haunting costumes with a light-up twist, Anjelika Temple returns to help Toya and James decide whose ghoulish getup is truly electrifying.

summaries.short: Ava, Cooper, and Sasha must turn paper lanterns into works of art before they get the chance to create an innovative small business stand.
summaries.full: Spunky 12-year-olds Ava, Cooper, and Sasha must turn paper lanterns into unique, whimsical works of art before the two most lit creators advance to an ambitious Craft Master Challenge: elevate the classic lemonade stand concept into an innovative small business idea. Pinterest goddess Joy Cho helps our judges decide whose stand and product sample are truly Craftrophia-worthy.

summaries.short: Adalyn, Sasha, and Sabrina transform plain paper-mache pinatas into monstrous creations before two of these 11-year-olds get the chance to turn ordinary dollhouses into miniature haunted abodes.
summaries.full: Adalyn, Sasha, and Sabrina transform boring paper-mache pinatas into terrifying monstrous creations before the Craft Master Challenge finds two of these 11-year-olds turning ordinary dollhouses into creepified haunted abodes. Anjelika Temple brings the fear factor to the judges’ panel as they make some bloodcurdling decisions.

summaries.full: Tida, Brodie, and Iris face-off in a couple of super sweet challenges. First up, we have a confection Quick Craft inspired by what guest judge Rosanna Pansino does best: baking! After incorporating bakery goods into edible masterpieces, two Craftestants channel their talents into adorable plushie-making.
